            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "There are three behaviors:\r\n\r\n- \"adhoc\" generates a new self-signed cert each time\r\n- paths to a cert and key file\r\n- an `SSLContext` object\r\n\r\nI'm not sure how far to go with the last one. I can accept a string then call `werkzeug.import_string`, but that's more limited than how the CLI imports the Flask object itself. It wouldn't support callables and would dump a stack trace on errors instead of showing it in the interactive debugger.\r\n\r\nWerkzeug has a `make_dev_cert` method to generate permanent files instead of the temporary ones with \"adhoc\". I'm wondering if I should expose this as a `flask make_local_cert` command."
        },
